===Etymology===
From {{der|en|sa|महाराष्ट्र}}, derived from {{m|sa|महा-}}, combining form of {{m|sa|महत्||great}} + {{m|sa|राष्ट्र}}, a dynasty that once ruled the area. In Sanskrit, the word {{m|sa|राष्ट्र}} means “nation” or “dominion”. Other theories indicate that the word "rāṣṭra" in this context derives from {{m|sa|रत्त}} (a corruption of “Rashtrakuta”, a dynasty that once ruled the area), a clan known as {{m|sa|राष्ट्रिक}} (found in some of {{w|King Ashoka}}’s inscriptions) or {{m|sa|रथ||chariot}}.

